# Install Virtual Machine Support for Debian

### Installation

~~~
sudo apt-get install qemu
sudo apt-get install libvirt
sudo apt-get install virt-manager
~~~


### Customization

~~~
sudo adduser <user> kvm
sudo adduser <user> libvirt
~~~

### Usage:

Start program: **virt-manaager**.

See [https://wiki.debian.org/KVM](https://wiki.debian.org/KVM)

* Menu File -> New Virtual Machine to create a machine. Allow creation / usage of new connection.

* Menu Edit (Bearbeiten) -> Connection Details (Verbindungsdetails)
* Tab "Virtual Networks": Check Checkbox "Autostart"

